Isn't it a wonderful vision that Stanislav Lamm already wrote up

01:20:04.800 --> 01:20:07.400
in the photo-rological Congress?

01:20:07.480 --> 01:20:11.920
That we take pills and then we virtualize our whole existence.

01:20:12.000 --> 01:20:14.080
Isn't that happening right now already?

01:20:14.160 --> 01:20:18.640
Like we translate ourselves much more in images than in writing.

01:20:18.720 --> 01:20:22.080
Like all the social media, much more like an image media

01:20:22.160 --> 01:20:23.840
than a written media.

01:20:23.840 --> 01:20:26.880
I agree, that's why, but we don't have time for this.

01:20:26.960 --> 01:20:33.080
That's why I much prefer Lamm's novel than Stalker the film.

01:20:33.160 --> 01:20:34.000
Yeah, me too.

01:20:34.080 --> 01:20:36.840
Novel is... Sorry, Solaris already.

01:20:36.920 --> 01:20:38.440
Solaris, Solaris, not Stalker.

01:20:38.520 --> 01:20:45.920
In the film, Tarkowski does the usual half-religious obsturantism.

01:20:46.000 --> 01:20:51.000
The object is just a mirror of the deepest desires of our soul.

01:20:51.120 --> 01:20:56.480
In Lamm's novel became a traumatic, external object

01:20:56.560 --> 01:21:00.120
which simply remains non-transparent.

01:21:00.200 --> 01:21:02.680
We know they are doing something with us,

01:21:02.760 --> 01:21:06.840
but we never learn at the end what.

01:21:06.920 --> 01:21:10.680
So, okay, let's not lose time.

01:21:10.760 --> 01:21:17.520
What I am just saying is that precisely every great philosophy

01:21:17.600 --> 01:21:23.120
always happens in the time of a crisis.

01:21:23.200 --> 01:21:24.160
Huge crisis.

01:21:24.240 --> 01:21:24.880
Sorry?

01:21:24.960 --> 01:21:25.680
Huge crisis, huge crisis.

01:21:25.760 --> 01:21:28.720
Plato, Aristotle, it's the end of Polish.

01:21:28.800 --> 01:21:30.520
It's already the decadence of Polish.

01:21:30.600 --> 01:21:32.800
And Hegel was quite aware.

01:21:32.880 --> 01:21:38.160
The new boost of philosophy from Kant to Hegel and later

01:21:38.240 --> 01:21:44.360
comes with the problems of Aufklärung and French Revolution.

01:21:44.360 --> 01:21:48.240
So, when with terror and so on, things went wrong, then...

01:21:48.320 --> 01:21:49.360
So, we need the crisis.

01:21:49.440 --> 01:21:49.840
Sorry?

01:21:49.920 --> 01:21:51.480
We need the crisis.

01:21:51.560 --> 01:21:54.040
To think properly, absolutely.

01:21:54.120 --> 01:21:58.280
I don't believe that to be a philosopher, you need peaceful time.

01:21:58.360 --> 01:22:01.600
No, true philosophy is for the times of emergency.

01:22:01.680 --> 01:22:06.160
But Kant, peaceful times, if it's so peaceful and you have no challenge at all,

01:22:06.240 --> 01:22:09.120
can be a great burden by itself as well.

01:22:09.200 --> 01:22:10.080
Absolutely.

01:22:10.160 --> 01:22:10.800
So, maybe...

01:22:10.880 --> 01:22:13.440
I'm afraid of this, absolutely.

01:22:13.440 --> 01:22:15.880
I mean, I cannot even...

01:22:15.960 --> 01:22:19.400
I'm an absolute workaholic, even tonight,

01:22:19.480 --> 01:22:22.440
because I was not able to do my work.

01:22:22.520 --> 01:22:24.000
I go back to Ljubljana and...

01:22:24.080 --> 01:22:25.600
And you finish it.

01:22:25.680 --> 01:22:26.960
Two hours minimum.

01:22:27.040 --> 01:22:29.000
It's very important to have a regime.

01:22:29.080 --> 01:22:29.520
Absolutely.

01:22:29.600 --> 01:22:30.560
Keeps you going.

01:22:30.640 --> 01:22:31.960
Because you need a task in life.

01:22:32.040 --> 01:22:37.280
I will end with a few obscenities, but take it friendly.

01:22:37.360 --> 01:22:38.840
It's not a bad joke.

01:22:38.920 --> 01:22:42.040
When a journalist asked me what's your favorite motto,

01:22:42.040 --> 01:22:44.360
I said, Arbeit macht frei.

01:22:44.440 --> 01:22:47.840
And then, of course, I said, I don't mean it in that way.

01:22:47.920 --> 01:22:51.320
But the Nazis brutally misused it.

01:22:51.400 --> 01:22:55.320
That work certainly didn't make you free.

01:22:55.400 --> 01:22:58.760
But the horror of the Nazis is that a motto,

01:22:58.840 --> 01:23:03.760
which is for me at least in itself a good one, free one,

01:23:03.840 --> 01:23:09.200
they misused it in the most horrible, imaginable way.

01:23:09.280 --> 01:23:10.440
But it's always like that.

01:23:10.440 --> 01:23:14.280
Sovereignty of interpretation means you control

01:23:14.360 --> 01:23:16.480
how you propagandize for things.

01:23:16.560 --> 01:23:22.040
So, but that's why I believe in failure, in mistakes, in mis-speaking.

01:23:22.120 --> 01:23:25.160
That's the only way, even in love.

01:23:25.240 --> 01:23:30.440
Don't you agree that when you declare love,

01:23:30.520 --> 01:23:33.480
this is for me the most traumatic moment always,

01:23:33.560 --> 01:23:36.760
when you declare love to somebody,

01:23:36.840 --> 01:23:41.200
if you don't do it with some oscillation, stumbling,

01:23:41.280 --> 01:23:42.800
there is something wrong.

01:23:42.880 --> 01:23:46.240
It means you are perfectly trained to do it.

01:23:46.320 --> 01:23:49.160
Did you see a stupid movie, otherwise I hated it,

01:23:49.240 --> 01:23:51.440
for weddings and the funeral.

01:23:51.520 --> 01:23:56.000
But there is a nice detail that when Hugh Grant declares love

01:23:56.080 --> 01:24:00.360
to Andy McDowell, he gets in his typical way,

01:24:00.440 --> 01:24:03.880
stumbles, repeats himself, that's how you declare love.

01:24:03.880 --> 01:24:10.800
So, the thing is, we reached the end, unfortunately.

01:24:10.880 --> 01:24:14.440
I want to ask you one last question.

01:24:14.520 --> 01:24:15.960
Will I kill myself?

01:24:16.040 --> 01:24:19.040
No, with the challenge attached to it,

01:24:19.120 --> 01:24:22.000
that you have to answer it really shortly.

01:24:22.080 --> 01:24:25.160
And we see, and if you can suffice,

01:24:25.240 --> 01:24:28.960
you were talking about the role of philosophy nowadays times,

01:24:29.040 --> 01:24:30.720
and we are very challenging times.

01:24:30.800 --> 01:24:34.400
So, do you generally, like, it's more like a yes or no question,

01:24:34.480 --> 01:24:39.760
do you generally think that the biggest challenge is

01:24:39.840 --> 01:24:46.640
that we live in times where we have a lot of reflexes,

01:24:46.720 --> 01:24:49.280
to counter stuff that is coming to us.

01:24:49.360 --> 01:24:54.640
And especially in times when there is a high pressure of reflex,

01:24:54.720 --> 01:24:59.120
that we should take our time to reflect instead of just reflex.

01:24:59.120 --> 01:25:00.360
Absolutley.

01:25:00.440 --> 01:25:05.880
This is why, to annoy many of my leftist friends,

01:25:05.960 --> 01:25:11.080
maybe you know it, this is my standard answer,

01:25:11.160 --> 01:25:14.200
like is Marxist-Physis XI.

01:25:14.280 --> 01:25:18.680
Philosophers have only interpreted the world, we have to change it.

01:25:18.760 --> 01:25:21.520
I claim that it's a correct phrase for today,

01:25:21.600 --> 01:25:23.320
just we should turn it around.

01:25:23.400 --> 01:25:28.120
In the 20th century, we wanted to change the world too fast,

01:25:28.120 --> 01:25:30.200
now we need to interpret it more.

01:25:30.280 --> 01:25:31.280
Exactly.

01:25:31.360 --> 01:25:37.560
Never were we so epistemologically, with our knowledge, disorientated.

01:25:37.640 --> 01:25:41.720
I ask you a simple question, what is China today?

01:25:41.800 --> 01:25:44.960
It's still communism, it's authoritarian capitalism.

01:25:45.040 --> 01:25:48.800
The basic orientation is missing.

01:25:48.880 --> 01:25:50.400
We have to finish now.

01:25:50.480 --> 01:25:52.680
Ladies and gentlemen, meine sehr verehrten Damen und Herren,

01:25:52.760 --> 01:25:55.120
danke, dass Sie sich so aufmerksam zugehört haben.

01:25:55.120 --> 01:26:00.480
Ich würde sagen, Genossen und Genossinnen.

01:26:00.560 --> 01:26:02.480
Fertig, danke.

01:26:13.560 --> 01:26:14.560
Danke.

01:26:14.640 --> 01:26:16.640
Das war ein Pleasure.

01:26:17.360 --> 01:26:19.560
Stop! Stop!

01:26:19.680 --> 01:26:23.640
Weil mit mir, du hast immer den Preis gespielt.

01:26:23.720 --> 01:26:25.160
Seit du das Applaus hast,

01:26:25.240 --> 01:26:29.240
werde ich dir eine wundervolle, dörrige Joke sagen.

01:26:29.320 --> 01:26:30.640
Das ist...

01:26:30.720 --> 01:26:31.720
Ja, ja.

01:26:31.800 --> 01:26:33.880
Wir müssen auf die Hände arbeiten.

01:26:33.960 --> 01:26:35.960
Du musst auf die Hände arbeiten.

01:26:36.040 --> 01:26:39.040
Nein, nein, aber eine dörrige Joke,

01:26:39.120 --> 01:26:42.680
die philosophisch korrekt ist.

01:26:42.760 --> 01:26:47.720
Eine starke Frau schenkt ihr Mann in der Sonne,

01:26:47.840 --> 01:26:52.040
und bringt mir ein paar Zigaretten aus der Trafik auf die Strecke.

01:26:52.120 --> 01:26:55.040
Der Mann geht raus, die Trafik ist zu nahe.

01:26:55.120 --> 01:26:59.960
Er geht zu einer Bar, um die Zigaretten zu kaufen.

01:27:00.040 --> 01:27:03.720
Da beginnt ein schönes Wetter, sie flirren.

01:27:03.800 --> 01:27:05.600
Sie enden in ihrer Fläche,

01:27:05.680 --> 01:27:08.800
schlug wie ein verrückter Tiltrin im Morgen.

01:27:08.880 --> 01:27:11.400
Dann sagt er, oh mein Gott, ich muss nach Hause.

01:27:11.480 --> 01:27:13.280
Was will ich zu meiner Frau sagen?

01:27:13.360 --> 01:27:14.920
Und er findet eine Lösung.

01:27:15.000 --> 01:27:16.240
Er sagt zu der Frau,

01:27:16.320 --> 01:27:21.000
ob du eine dieser, wenn du einen Puder machen willst,

01:27:21.880 --> 01:27:24.320
okay, eine Bohlinge für Bohlinge.

01:27:24.400 --> 01:27:27.440
Okay, er setzt das an und geht nach Hause.

01:27:27.520 --> 01:27:29.800
Be careful for the dialectic now.

01:27:29.880 --> 01:27:32.400
Die Frau fragt ihm, wo war du?

01:27:32.480 --> 01:27:33.600
Sucht eine lange Zeit.

01:27:33.680 --> 01:27:38.560
Und er sagt, ich bin raus, die Trafik war zu nahe.

01:27:38.640 --> 01:27:41.080
Ich bin zu einer Bar, ich habe mit einer Frau geflirtet,

01:27:41.160 --> 01:27:43.000
wir haben ein verrückter Tiltrin.

01:27:43.080 --> 01:27:44.400
Und du weißt, was ist der Effekt?

01:27:44.480 --> 01:27:48.440
Die Frau sagt, warum bist du so miserably lieb mit mir?

01:27:48.520 --> 01:27:49.640
Ich sehe die Puder,

01:27:49.720 --> 01:27:52.800
du warst mit deinen Freunden Bohlinge.

01:27:52.880 --> 01:27:55.280
Das ist die politische Art,

01:27:55.360 --> 01:27:57.640
um die Wahrheit zu erzählen,

01:27:57.720 --> 01:28:00.000
in eine Weise, die die Enemene zu confusieren.

01:28:00.080 --> 01:28:01.640
Das ist für mich.

01:28:09.200 --> 01:28:11.600
Professor, Dr. Slavo Shisha.

01:28:12.160 --> 01:28:13.280
Danke.

01:28:13.360 --> 01:28:15.360
Danke.

